This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning, which are both covered by the Computer Science sub-category of "cs.CL" (Computation and Language). The use of pre-trained word embeddings also falls under the sub-categories of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning) and "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the performance of NMT systems, which could be categorized under "cs.NE" (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of word embeddings in image captioning, which could be related to "cs.CV" (Computer Vision).
